# Spec Sync Rule

Scope: **`docs/specs/` only** (`payboard.md` is the master spec; feature specs live alongside it). Do not update `CLAUDE.md` or `AGENTS.md`.

After completing a task, check whether the change is **spec-worthy**:

| Category | Examples |
|----------|----------|
| Major features | New page/route, pay-date-card capability, archive tab, settings section |
| Workflow | New/changed steps, bill states, auth flow, create-month flow, template save rules |
| Layout / IA | Sidebar structure, page sections, column layout, modals vs expand-in-place |
| Visual / style | Design tokens in `globals.css`, themes, header palette, typography, motion rules |
| Copy | Nav labels, headings, CTAs, empty/loading states, user-facing errors |
| Data model / domain | Fields in `lib/types.ts`, persistence rules, mute vs paid semantics, board statuses |

**Do NOT update specs for:** bug fixes, refactors, type-only cleanups, performance, deps/config, tests, internal renames with no UX change, one-off Tailwind spacing tweaks.

**Borderline:** mention in your response; don't edit the spec unless the user confirms.

## Routing table

| Code area | Primary spec | Section hints |
|-----------|--------------|---------------|
| `components/sidebar.tsx`, `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` | `payboard.md` | Layout → Sidebar Navigation |
| `components/board/*`, `components/modules/*`, `app/dashboard/page.tsx` | `payboard.md` | Layout → Pay Board / Pay Date Card; Workflow → bill states & card menu |
| `components/income-expenses/*`, `app/dashboard/bills-and-income/*` | `payboard.md` | Layout → Bills & Income; Workflow → mute/archive/source-of-truth |
| `components/debt-tracker/*`, `app/dashboard/debt-tracker/*` | `payboard.md` | Layout → Debt Tracker; Workflow → table behavior |
| `components/archive/*`, `app/dashboard/archive/*` | `payboard.md` | Layout → Archive; Workflow → restore/delete |
| `app/dashboard/settings/page.tsx` | `payboard.md` | Layout → Settings Overview |
| `components/settings/*`, `app/dashboard/settings/organize/*` | `payboard.md` | Layout → Organize Lists |
| `components/templates/*`, `app/dashboard/settings/templates/**` | `template-system.md` first; nav in `payboard.md` if needed | Templates Page, Editor, Create Month subsections |
| `app/sign-in/**`, `app/sign-up/**`, `proxy.ts`, `lib/session.ts` | `payboard.md` | Workflow → auth/session bullets |
| `lib/types.ts`, `lib/useMyPayBoard.ts`, `lib/supabase/mappers/*` | `payboard.md` | Overview → Key types / Data & persistence; Workflow → domain rules |
| `app/globals.css`, `components/ThemeInitScript.tsx`, `lib/userPrefs.ts` | `payboard.md` | Visual / Style → tokens, themes, typography |
| `components/modules/header-colors.ts` | `payboard.md` | Visual / Style → header palette; Layout → card header |

**New major surface with no spec:** create `docs/specs/{feature-name}.md` from `docs/specs/_template.md`. Link once from `payboard.md` Overview or Open Questions.

## Update procedure

1. Pick the best spec file from the routing table.
2. Patch **only** the affected subsection (Layout, Workflow, Visual / Style, Copy, or Overview for schema). No full rewrites, no changelog commentary.
3. Keep tone operational and route-accurate (e.g. `/dashboard/settings/templates`).
4. Bump `**Last updated:**` to today's date in each edited spec.
5. End major feature tasks with a one-line note: which spec sections were updated, or "no spec update — refactor only".
